100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On November 5, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, discussing measures to enhance global security and prevent future conflicts. In the United States, the ongoing debate surrounding Prohibition continued to stir public sentiment, with various states grappling with enforcement challenges. Meanwhile, the British Empire faced tensions in India as nationalist movements gained momentum, calling for greater self-governance.
